    "It can generate signal wave patterns of various sizes and create a series of data sequences with local features at various periods, where each component is a stationary IMF.",
    "Two criteria must be satisfied by each IMFs component: (1) the mean value of the envelope formed by its local maximum and minimum must be zero at any moment, and (2) the number of extreme points in the entire dataset must be the same as zero-crossing points or vary by at most one.",
    "For a time-series sequence (t), the key steps of CEEMDAN decomposition are as follows:",
    "• At time m, we introduce white noise W m (t) to the original signal X m (t).",
    "where M represents the number of realizations."
